'''Rooze Disease''' was an affliction, one of the deadliest in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], caused by the deadly rooze germ agent that affected [[Human/Legends|Humans]]. After the germ infected the body, it would cause the victim's health to slowly deteriorate until, if not cured after roughly three [[Galactic Standard Calendar|standard days]], it disintegrated the body within seconds. During these days the patient would feel dizziness and a strange sensation that his or her hands faded away. As it happened, [[Kobok/Legends|Koboks]] like [[Gaff]] were immune.

It was first tested as a biological weapon by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] during the [[Mavvan Conflict]] but it eliminated the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial troops]] along with the rebels it was targeted against and was never used again. [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Bisad Koong|Koong]] of [[Tawntoom]] on [[Roon/Legends|Roon]] made the same mistake and unleashed it on the pastoral [[Umboo]] province, infecting himself in the process. [[Terrinald Screed/Legends|Terrinald Screed]] and his [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]], however, evaded being infected during this instance via a breath mask and their armor, respectively.

[[Nilz Yomm]] eventually discovered a cure for the germ. In addition to its medicinal value, a Kobok heavily dosed with the substance will begin to manically laugh uncontrollably, unable to perform any other action while under its effect.

==Behind the scenes==
In the subtitles of ''[[Treasure of the Hidden Planet]]'' on side two of the [[Star Wars: Droids: The Adventures of R2-D2 and C-3PO|''Star Wars Droids'']] [[Star Wars home video releases|DVD]], "rooze" is written "roos."

